                            <comment id="79240" author="pjones" created="Thu, 13 Mar 2014 15:07:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Landed for 2.5.1 and 2.6&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="79056" author="jamesanunez" created="Tue, 11 Mar 2014 22:23:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Mike, &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Your patch works with -Rssh and gets me past the copytool start up.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="79044" author="mjmac" created="Tue, 11 Mar 2014 21:22:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sigh. In dealing with the nuances of running backgrounded processes via mrsh, I inadvertently introduced a hard dependency on it. Environments with -Rssh (or, indeed, any valid non-mrsh $PDSH) shouldn&apos;t be using the workaround.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The following fix has been validated to work with -Rmrsh: &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/9587&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/9587&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;James, please confirm when possible that the fix also works with -Rssh.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="79037" author="pjones" created="Tue, 11 Mar 2014 20:34:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Mike is looking into this&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
